      • setExplicitTimeout

        public void setExplicitTimeout(long timeoutInSeconds)
        This method is to set member variable used for explicit timeout. Explicit timeout specify the amount of time the driver should wait for a certain condition to occur before proceeding.
        Parameters:
        timeoutInSeconds - Amount of time in seconds to wait.

      • setTimeout

        public void setTimeout(MasterHelper.TimeoutType type,
              long time,
              java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit unit)
        This method is to set the Implicit timeout or Script timeout or PageLoad timeout. Implicit timeout specify the amount of time the driver should wait when searching for an element. Script timeout specify the amount of time the driver should wait for an asynchronous script to finish. PageLoad timeout specify the amount of time the driver should wait for a page load to complete.
        Parameters:
        Type - Parameter to tell the type of timeout to set.
        time - The amount of time to set.
        unit - The unit of measure for time.

      • setText

        public void setText(org.openqa.selenium.WebElement Element,
           java.lang.String NewText)
        This method sets the text for a given WebElement. There are problems with WebElement.sendKeys() where events do not fire quickly enough if the entire string is sent in one call. This method sends the string one character at a time to slow down the speed of the typing.
        Parameters:
        element - The WebElement whose text is being cleared
